        "author_association": "MEMBER",
        "body": "Yes, you can avoid filesystem operations on the client right now, but the bytes are still streamed to the client, where any parsing and graph building are done. This means no improvement in IO parallelism, it purely solves the \"workers see different files to me\" situation (because of auth, etc).",
